    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-05-09T14:06:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-05-09T14:06:00-05:00" n="469"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d469">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">110.11 DU/5–954: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">United States Delegation</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d469fn1">Drafted by the Secretary of State. Repeated to
                        Paris as telegram 4002 and to Saigon as telegram 2233.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret<lb/>priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-05-09T15:06:00-04:00"
                            >May 9, 1954—3:06 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Tedul1">Tedul</gloss> 46. For Under Secretary from Secretary.
                    Re <gloss target="#t_Dulte1">Dulte</gloss> 56.<note n="2" xml:id="d469fn2">Dated
                        May 9, <ref target="#pg_737">p. 737</ref>.</note> Following is memo of my
                    conversation with <persName corresp="#p_BH1">Bonnet</persName> May 8:<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d469fn3">For the text of memorandum of conversation, see <ref
                            target="frus1952-54v13p1">volume <hi rend="smallcaps">xiii</hi>
                        </ref>.</note>
                    <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“I called on Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_BH1">Bonnet</persName> at
                            his residence, he being indisposed. We spoke of my speech the night
                            before which he commended. I said I assumed that the parallel with Korea
                            had been noted by him and he said that it had. I said that this was as
                            far as I thought it wise to go publicly in indicating what had on many
                            previous occasions been made clear, namely that the United States was
                            prepared to sit down and talk with the French about what the French
                            called “internationalizing” the war and working out a real partnership
                            basis. I said that as far as the immediate present was concerned, I
                            assumed that the French Government would still not want this. However,
                            they might change their mind after the full harshness of probable
                            Communist terms was revealed. Then this might seem to them an
                            alternative worth exploring. I wanted the French to know that such
                            explorations would be acceptable to the United States.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
